background.$description: Default background color for screens and large surfaces.

error.$description: Color for error states, used on elements like error text and icons.

error-container.$description: Fill color for error container elements like error banners.

inverse-on-surface.$description: Color for text and icons on inverse surface backgrounds.

inverse-primary.$description: Primary color used on inverse surface, e.g. buttons on snackbars.

inverse-surface.$description: Background for elements that require reverse contrast, such as snackbars.

on-background.$description: Color for text and icons displayed on the background.

on-error.$description: Color for text and icons on error-colored elements.

on-error-container.$description: Color for text and icons on error container elements.

on-primary.$description: Color for text and icons on primary-colored elements like filled buttons.

on-primary-container.$description: Color for text and icons on primary container elements like tonal buttons.

on-primary-fixed.$description: Color for text and icons on primary fixed elements, constant across themes.

on-primary-fixed-variant.$description: Lower-emphasis color for text and icons on primary fixed elements.

on-secondary.$description: Color for text and icons on secondary-colored elements.

on-secondary-container.$description: Color for text and icons on secondary container elements.

on-secondary-fixed.$description: Color for text and icons on secondary fixed elements, constant across themes.

on-secondary-fixed-variant.$description: Lower-emphasis color for text and icons on secondary fixed elements.

on-surface.$description: High-emphasis color for text and icons on surface backgrounds.

on-surface-variant.$description: Medium-emphasis color for text and icons on surface variant backgrounds.

on-tertiary.$description: Color for text and icons on tertiary-colored elements.

on-tertiary-container.$description: Color for text and icons on tertiary container elements.

on-tertiary-fixed.$description: Color for text and icons on tertiary fixed elements, constant across themes.

on-tertiary-fixed-variant.$description: Lower-emphasis color for text and icons on tertiary fixed elements.

outline.$description: Subtle color for borders and dividers to create visual separation.

outline-variant.$description: Lower-emphasis border color used for decorative dividers.

primary.$description: Main brand color, used for key components like filled buttons and active states.

primary-container.$description: Fill color for large primary elements like cards and tonal buttons.

primary-fixed.$description: Fixed primary color that stays the same in light and dark themes.

primary-fixed-dim.$description: Dimmed variant of the fixed primary color for lower emphasis.

scrim.$description: Color overlay for modals and dialogs to obscure background content.

secondary.$description: Accent color for less prominent elements like filter chips and selections.

secondary-container.$description: Fill color for secondary container elements like tonal buttons and input fields.

secondary-fixed.$description: Fixed secondary color that stays the same in light and dark themes.

secondary-fixed-dim.$description: Dimmed variant of the fixed secondary color for lower emphasis.

shadow.$description: Color for elevation shadows applied to surfaces and components.

surface.$description: Default surface color for cards, sheets, and dialogs.

surface-bright.$description: Brightest surface variant, used for elevated surfaces in dark themes.

surface-container.$description: Middle-emphasis container color for grouping related content.

surface-container-high.$description: Higher-emphasis container color for elements like cards.

surface-container-highest.$description: Highest-emphasis container color for text fields and other input areas.

surface-container-low.$description: Lower-emphasis container color for subtle surface groupings.

surface-container-lowest.$description: Lowest-emphasis container, typically the lightest surface in light theme.

surface-dim.$description: Dimmest surface variant, used for recessed areas or dark theme backgrounds.

surface-tint.$description: Tint color applied to surfaces for subtle primary color elevation overlay.

surface-variant.$description: Alternative surface color for differentiated areas like sidebar backgrounds.

tertiary.$description: Third accent color for complementary elements that balance primary and secondary.

tertiary-container.$description: Fill color for tertiary container elements like complementary cards.

tertiary-fixed.$description: Fixed tertiary color that stays the same in light and dark themes.

tertiary-fixed-dim.$description: Dimmed variant of the fixed tertiary color for lower emphasis.
